        <div class="max-width">
            <h2 class="title">Module 1</h2>
            <div class="about-content">
                <div class="column left">
                    <div class="text">Hosting a website using RaspberryPi
<span class="typing-2"></span></div>
                    <p>Introduction:<br>&emsp;&emsp;
When a webite is hosted using RaspberryPi, all the systems which are connected in the same network as the device, can access this website using the IP address of RaspberryPi. The website we are demonstrating is a basic implementation of a HTML - CSS page using apache software.
<br><br>
Details:<br>&emsp;&emsp;
The main goal for the Apache service is to answer requests on HTTP and HTTPS ports of your Raspberry Pi. HTTP and HTTPS are the main protocols on the Internet for web surfing. It works because Apache is here to respond to your browser requests on ports 80 and 443.
When Apache receives a request on your Raspberry Pi IP address, it has to display something, depending on your Apache configuration. Typically, it’s an HTML page for your website or the app you’re using on the Raspberry Pi.
.</p>
                    
                </div>
