    <section class="about" id="about">
        <div class="max-width">
            <h2 class="title">Module 2</h2>
            <div class="about-content">
                <div class="column left">
                    <div class="text">File Transfer using RaspberryPi
<span class="typing-2"></span></div>
                    <p>Introduction:<br>&emsp;&emsp;
We utilize a Raspberry Pi as our server for storing encrypted files via Python. It enables multiple devices within the same network to connect to and access stored data.
<br><br>
Details:<br>&emsp;&emsp;
Rather than utilizing the FTP protocol, we transmit files by breaking them into 128-byte chunks and maintaining an uninterrupted connection through the TCP protocol. The client is capable of accessing and downloading files from the server, but the download occurs only when the file matches the one originally uploaded by the client.
The client uses a Merkle tree data structure to verify the integrity of the files, ensuring that any changes or alterations are easily detectable through the structure of the tree.
</p>
                    
                </div>
